The '''Ministry of Science and Higher Education of the Russian Federation''' ({{lang-ru|Министерство науки и высшего образования Российской Федерации}}) is a ministry established in May 2018 as a result of splitting the [[Ministry of Education and Science (Russia)|Ministry of Education and Science]], existed from March 2004, into the two agencies. The second simultaneously emerged agency is the [[Ministry of Education (Russia)|Ministry of Education]] sometimes called "of General Education" or "of Enlightenment". The Ministry of Science and Higher Education is responsible for a state control over the scientific institutions and the university-level education in the [[Russian Federation]]. Particularly, all institutes of the [[Russian Academy of Sciences]] are now under jurisdiction of this Ministry. It is headquartered in [[Moscow]]. Mikhail Kotyukov is appointed to serve as a Minister.<ref name="minsite">{{cite web |url= http://government.ru/en/department/388/events/ |title= Brief info on the Ministry of Science and Higher Education |author= |publisher= Website of the Russian Government |date= |accessdate= 2018-08-06 |quote= }}</ref><ref name="establ">{{cite web |url= http://tass.com/politics/1005075 |title= Putin signs decrees on appointing new Russian cabinet members |author= |publisher= [[TASS]] |date= 2018-05-18 |accessdate= 2018-08-06 |quote= }}</ref>
