{{Infobox Radio Show | show_name = The Mr Science Show | image = | imagesize = | caption = ''The Mr Science Show'' | format = [[Talk radio|Talk Radio]] / [[Podcasts|Podcast]] | runtime = 10 minutes | creator = Marc West | starring = Marc West | country = {{flagicon|Australia}} Australia {{flagicon|China}} People's Republic of China | home_station = [[China Radio International]] | first_aired = 2006 | last_aired = present | num_episodes = 100+ | website = http://www.mrscienceshow.com }} {{distinguish|text=[[The Mr. Science Show]], a lecture based science television program for children}}
'''Mr Science Show''' is an [[Australian]] [[science]] [[podcast]].<ref>[http://www.mrscienceshow.com Mr Science Show]</ref> The show originated on [[China Radio International]]<ref>China Radio International, "[http://english.cri.cn/4026/2007/06/11/202@237136.htm]", 2007-06-11.</ref> in 2006, and was broadcast on [[China Drive]] until 2008, at which point it became a podcast. The show in [[People's Republic of China|China]] was broadcast in English and produced in [[Beijing]], with creator Marc West interviewed over the phone. Currently, the podcast is produced in [[Australia]] by Marc West.<ref>Robbins, Gary. [http://www.ocregister.com/ocregister/healthscience/columns/article_1234529.php A peak at podcasts], ''[[Orange County Register]]'', 2006-08-05.</ref> The show was originally produced by [[James West (Australian journalist)|James West]].
Archived versions of the show are available on the [http://www.mrscienceshow.com Mr Science Show site] and through the podcast on [http://phobos.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=159797886 iTunes].
