'''Olaus Petriskolan''' is a Swedish school in [[Örebro]]. It is a public school that opened in 1908 under the name "Norra folkskolan". It was created by architect [[Carl Nissen]]. Its name was changed in 1925.<ref>[http://na.se/stadsliv/orebrofragan/1.288388-op-skolan-eller-gumaeliusskolan- Skolan eller] na.se Retrieved 15 October 2018</ref>
